Step 1 : Create the gallery placeholder view
from django.shortcuts import render
def gallery_placeholder(request):
    return render(request, 'home/gallery_placeholder.html')

Step 2 : Create the gallery placeholder 
<html>
<head>
    <title>Gallery - Coming Soon</title>
</head>
<body>  
    <h1>Our Gallery</h1>
    <p>We're curating some delicious visualsfor you!</p>
    <p>Stay tuned - our gallery will be available soon.</p>
</body>
</html>

Step 3 : Add URL for gallery
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('gallery/', views.gallery_placeholder, name='gallery_placeholder'),
]

Step 4 : Add a placeholder section
<section id = "gallery-placeholder">
     <h2>Gallery</h2>
     <p>Our gallery is coming soon! You'll be able to see our best dishes here.</p>
     <a href="{% url 'gallery_placeholder' %}">View Gallery</a>
</section>
